This paper is primarily focused on access control in mobile platforms, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of context-aware mediation systems, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of user interface inspection in access control decisions, which could fall under the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the implementation and evaluation of the proposed system, which could fall under the sub-categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and cryptography and security (cs.CY).
